The paper discusses the security challenges of cloud computing, specifically focusing on the virtual infrastructure. This makes it highly likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of virtualization technology in cloud computing, which suggests it could also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexities of the virtual infrastructure, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The use of internet-based services and the need for on-demand access to computing resources suggests it could also belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the need for new virtualization-aware security solutions, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
